cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper discusses the design of adversarially resilient classifiers, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer security and cryptography (cs.CR), computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). The paper specifically focuses on feature engineering, which is a key aspect of machine learning, and also discusses the use of adversarial attacks, which is a topic in computer security and cryptography. The use of feature extractors and classifiers also falls under the sub-categories of computer vision and pattern recognition, artificial intelligence, and neural and evolutionary computing.
